  "prompt": "Knock knee cause any problem in Delhi police si selection?",
  "response": "Knock knees, or genu valgum, can potentially impact your eligibility for selection in certain physical jobs, including police forces. For positions like the Delhi Police Sub-Inspector (SI), candidates are usually required to meet specific physical and medical standards. These standards are outlined in the recruitment notification or guidelines.\n\nIf you have knock knees, it might be assessed during the medical examination phase of the selection process. The severity of the condition will be taken into account, and officers performing the examination will determine whether it affects your ability to perform the duties required for the position. If the condition is minor and does not impede physical activities, it might not be a disqualifying factor. However, if it significantly impacts physical movement or could lead to long-term health issues, it could be considered a concern.\n\nIt's advisable to consult the specific recruitment guidelines for the Delhi Police SI position and consider seeking a medical opinion to understand the extent of your condition. If you're aiming for this role, addressing any medical issues beforehand with appropriate treatment or corrective measures, if recommended by a healthcare professional, might be beneficial.",
